section.section:
At a minimum, the Department shall include in the database:
the Standards;
local amendments to the Standards;
the State Fire Prevention Code adopted by the State Fire Prevention Commission under Title 6 of this article;
fire prevention codes adopted by local jurisdictions;
the Electrical Code required under Subtitle 6 of this title;
local amendments to the Electrical Code;
the Energy Code defined under the Energy Conservation Building Standards Act, Title 7, Subtitle 4 of the Public Utilities Article;
local code provisions that are more restrictive than the Energy Code defined under the Energy Conservation Building Standards Act;
information compiled by the Department under paragraph (2) of this subsection;
the Maryland Building Rehabilitation Code;
local amendments to the Maryland Building Rehabilitation Code; and
proposed federal or State legislation of which the Department is aware and that directly affects the construction industry.
